<h1><strong>CM Answers Pro </strong></h1>
 <p><strong>A Pro version of CM Answers is <a href="http://answers.cminds.com/"  target="_blank">available here</a></strong></p>
<h2>Features (Pro Version Only)</h2>
<ul>
<ul>
	<li><strong>Social Media Registration Integration</strong>- Integrates with Facebook, Google+, and LinkedIn profiles. (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/image1.png" target="_blank">image-1</a>) (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/cm-answers-image2.png" target="_blank">image-2</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Shortcodes</strong>- Generates a Questions List by using a Shortcode: cma-questions with additional parameters. For example, limit=10 author=123 sort=hottest (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/cm-answers-shortcode-example/" target="_blank">Demo</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>User Dashboard</strong>- Adds "My Questions" and "My Answers" dashboards to the user profile page by using Shortcodes: cma-my-questions and cma-my-answers. (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/cm-answers-image3.png" target="_blank">image</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Categories</strong>- Ability to add categories and display them using a Shortcode. cat=catname (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/cm-answers-shortcode-example/" target="_blank">Demo</a>), (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/answers" target="_blank">Demo in Questions Index</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Widgets</strong>- Widget integration that can sort and display hottest questions, most viewed, most recent answers and more. (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/cm-answers-image4.png" target="_blank">image</a>), (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/answers" target="_blank">Demo in Questions Index</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>User Posting Meter</strong> -Ability to add the user's profile of the number of posted questions and answers that the user has contributed displayed beside their user name. (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/cm-answers-image5.png" target="_blank">image</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Show/Hide Views</strong>- Administrator can choose to hide or show the number of views that a topic has. (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/cm-answers-image6.png" target="_blank">image</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Moderation</strong>- Administrators can define a list of users who are exempt and can post without any need of moderation. (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/cm-answers-image7.png" target="_blank">image</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Multisite</strong>- Supports multisites.</li>
	<li><strong>Public User Profile</strong>- Automatically generates a public profile page containing all the questions and answers a user has posted, with a link to his or her social media profile. (<a href="http://www.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/cm-answers-image8.png" target="_blank">image</a>), (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/contributor/admin/" target="_blank">Demo</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Gravatar</strong> - Ability to display a Gravatar near the user's name and in the user's profile. </li>
	<li><strong>Order Answers</strong> - Shows and sorts all answers in ascending or descending order. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99D" target="_blank">Image from Settings</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Attachments</strong> - Accepts file attachments when posting a question. Limits for file types and sizes. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99A.png" target="_blank">Image</a>), (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99B" target="_blank">Image from Settings</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Localization Support</strong> - Frontend (user side) is localized.</li>
	<li><strong>View Count Control</strong> - Controls how a view count is tabulated (by view or by session). (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99C" target="_blank">Image from Settings</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Ajax Support</strong> - Uses a Shortcode that displays the Category, supported by Ajax. Views of categories fit within the current site template. <a href="http://jumpstartcto.com/cm-answers-ajax-example" target="_blank">See Example</a></li>
	<li><strong>Gratitude Message</strong> - Does not include our Gratitude Message in the footer.</li>
	<li><strong>Tags</strong> - Tags are fully supported. Administrators can control the appearance of tags with an available Tags widget. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/answers" target="_blank">Demo - Widget on the right</a>), (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99E" target="_blank">Image</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Sticky Questions</strong> - Supports sticky questions with an administrator defined background color. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/answers" target="_blank">Demo - First question is sticky</a>), (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99F" target="_blank">Image When Admin edit question post</a>) , (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99H" target="_blank">Image from settings</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Code Snippets in Posts</strong> -  Support for code snippets and custom background color. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/answers/code-example/" target="_blank">Demo of code inside a question</a>), (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99G" target="_blank">Image from settings</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Homepage</strong> - Supports options to define CM Answers as the Site or Blog homepage  (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99M" target="_blank">Image from settings</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Permalink</strong> - Customizable CM Answers permalink. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99N" target="_blank">Image from settings</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Disclaimer</strong> -Added Disclaimer support for first time users. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99O" target="_blank">Image from settings</a>) , (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/wp-content/uploads/edd/Answers99P" target="_blank">Image when disclaimer appears</a>)</li>
	<li><strong>Social Share</strong> - Includes a social share widget in the question page. (<a href="http://answers.cminds.com/answers/code-example/" target="_blank">Demo</a>)</li>
</ul>
